rComments: Challenging, caring professor, one of the best I've had.  Introduced me to difficult concepts, helped me to get into graduate school.  Giving of her time and energy to all students.
Great Prof!  Had her for a synthesis class, so not a ton of teaching.

My love of education began with Prof. Robertson.  She may not be every undergrad (B.Ed.) students cup of tea, but her grad and Ph.D. classes are amazing.  She works in very cool spaces and brings in film studies concepts which you won't encounter elsewhere in the Faculty of Education.  Not easy readings, but worth the struggle.

I did not have her as a prof, but I had to take a course that was designed by her and relied on some of her writing. It was not the least bit helpful, and the students in the class were extremely frustrated.
AMAZING teacher. Truly loves her field and inspires one to be a caring and approachable teacher.
